Chemische Fabrik Budenheim KG
Budenheim is a global specialty chemicals company with production sites in Germany, China, Mexico, USA, Spain and The Netherlands. Building on an innovative portfolio of products and services, Budenheim offers sustainable solutions for a broad range of applications. These include the fields of nutrition, health, safety, and perservation of resources. In close cooperation with its customers, the chemical specialits develops solutions for a better life and sets basis for enduring profitability, consistency and environmental responsibility.

Budenheim maintains a leading position in the market for halogen-free flame retardants. Safe by design, BUDIT® halogen-free flame retardant solutions provide non-toxic and non-corrosive fire protection with minimized release of smoke and an outstanding ecological profile. Circular economy demands the recyclability of flame retarded plastics. BUDIT® proved effective fire retardancy over multiple recycling cycles. Designed for engineering plastics, BUDIT® halogen-free flame retardants are typically used in E&E, building and construction and automotive applications and meet highest fire safety standards. QolorTech® masterbatches provide innovative solutions for upcycling and recycling, including the overcoloring of PCR materials. They specialize in high-performance combination batches that integrate both color and functional masterbatch properties. Specialty grades of QolorTech® are manufactured for laser marking/welding applications, foaming and packaging solutions. Budenheim provides tailored solutions that meet the evolving needs of the plastics industry, delivering efficiency while aligning with sustainability goals.
