BENVIC SAS
Benvic is a leading international polymer compounder with over 60 years of technical expertise in the formulation and manufacture of PVC compounds, engineering plastics, biobased plastics, compostables and medical applications.

The Benvic material portfolio consists of more than 3,000 products. These are spread across 7 main areas : ProVinyl, Plantura, Linkflex, Dotcore, Dot-R, Dotflex & ChemMed.

Benvic’s PVC compounds represent the historical core of the company and are grouped under the business line ProVinyl, comprising rigid, flexible and recycled grades.

Through an ambitious expansion policy, Benvic also now produces technical materials other than PVC, for various application segments. Benvic’s range of polypropylene compounds - PP compounds (Dotcore), thermoplastic elastomers (Dotflex), biopolymers (Plantura) and halogen-free polymers for electrical wiring (Linkflex HF), are key examples of this.

The challenge of environmental transition involves offering solutions with a lower footprint. Benvic is working to continuously improve the impact of its existing ranges. The development of products incorporating ingredients from mechanical recycling is a priority for Benvic, ensuring expertise in the regeneration of post-use materials.

With eight manufacturing sites in Europe and the United States, Benvic works with its customers to co-develop sustainable, high performance solutions through local technical support and process expertise.

Benvic contributes to the technical, economic and environmental performance of your products.
This is Benvic''s mission: ‘Redesigning plastics. For good.’
