Universal Straw for Extru', products_services = 'Exhibitors & Products | Solinatra is a next-generation biopolymer that delivers the performance of traditional plastics without leaving a trace. Made from renewable, responsibly sourced materials and engineered to be 100% free from fossil-fuel plastics, ... | Solinatra is proud of our recognition as a top innovator, being the third winner in the KVK Innovation Top 100 Awards 2024 in the Circular Economy category. The KVK Innovation Top 100 publishes an annual list of 100 innovations of small and medium-sized enterprises in the Netherlands. All nominees are assessed on their impact on industry and society, originality, availability, realised turnover, and growth potential. Among hundreds of innovative companies, Solinatra was recognised in the Circular Economy category for developing 100% natural, compostable, and biodegradable materials that provide truly sustainable alternatives to plastics. Products made of Solinatra are broken down into nutrient-rich soil in both industrial and home composting systems without leaving microplastics behind. This process promotes a circular economy and significantly contributes to reducing plastic pollution and regenerating ecosystems."This award is a tremendous honour for our team. To be awarded in the Circular Economy category is a powerful support and motivation to continue our mission to replace polluting plastics with our innovative biomaterials that are fully natural, biodegradable, and circular by design. Together with our partners and customers, we remain committed to transforming industries to a healthier, more sustainable future," said Robert I. de Jong, CEO of Solinatra. Solinatra: Made for circularitySolinatra represents true circularity. Made from agricultural byproducts and plant-based ingredients, Solinatra integrates seamlessly into existing manufacturing systems, including injection moulding, thermoforming, and extrusion. Our applications span a wide range of products in diverse industries, such as cutlery, straws, coffee capsules, plant pots, and more, enabling brands and manufacturers to transition away from plastic without compromising convenience or environmental impact.As the world increasingly looks forward to circular solutions, Solinatra is grateful to be the Third Winner of KVK Innovation Top 100 2024. This strengthens Solinatra to provide an accessible and scalable solution for brands and manufacturers across the globe.If you’re exploring truly sustainable alternatives to transform your business, we’d be delighted to hear from you—let’s take the next step toward a more sustainable future together! About SolinatraSolinatra, the Dutch sustainable innovation company, specialises in replacing fossil-based plastics with 100% natural, plant-based, PFAS-free materials to avoid plastic waste and reduce CO2 emissions. These materials offer all the advantages of plastic without the disadvantages and are fully biodegradable and compostable, leaving behind no microplastics.  For more information, please visit www.solinatra.com | Exhibitors & Products | Digital Services Act (DSA)', hall = '14', stand = 'A50', contact_persons = '[{"name": "Chris May", "role": "Sales Director", "email": "", "phone": "", "additional_info": ""}, {"name": "", "role": "", "email": "", "phone": "", "additional_info": ""}]'::jsonb, scraping_timestamp = '2025-09-18T03:06:38.832639', success = true, scraping_status = 'completed', data_source = 'ultimate_scraping'
